Machakos County Assembly has ejected Mua MCA Francis Ngunga from the house's leader of majority seat. The MCAs replaced Ngunga with Kinanie MCA Mark Mwendo, also elected on Wiper party ticket. The motion to oust him was sponsored by MCA Tariq Mulatia. The MCAs accused Ngunga of working closely with Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua despite being a Wiper MCA. They also accused him of pushing for construction of new assembly chambers worth Sh300 million. Ngunga dismissed the claims terming them petty and baseless. He said he will move to court to seek justice.  Click here for the latest political news 